				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">You can program NES and Famicom programs in C, although it doesn't work as well as using assembly language for this purpose. ASM6 is one assembler, and there are others; I happen to like Unofficial MagicKit, which uses a nonstandard syntax although I think it is a better syntax and I have added many features, and will add even more improvement too. Both assemblers have some features the other lacks, although it can be corrected. There are a number of other assemblers too, and even higher-level programming languages available. You should also look at the documentation in the wiki to learn how the hardware works. If you want to test on real hardware, then you also need a cartridge.</div>

					
						<div class="postbody"><br />_________________<br /><a href="gopher://zzo38computer.org/" class="postlink">.</a></div>
					<br clear="all" /><br />

