						<div class="postbody">There are a few of us who do some NES development in C. If you are more comfortable with C it might be a reasonable place to start.<br /><br />Shiru wrote an article: <a href="http://shiru.untergrund.net/articles/programming_nes_games_in_c.htm" class="postlink">http://shiru.untergrund.net/articles/programming_nes_games_in_c.htm</a><br /><br />I haven't written a guide, though I did make one NES program in C so far which is open source: <a href="http://rainwarrior.ca/music/coltrane_src.zip" class="postlink">http://rainwarrior.ca/music/coltrane_src.zip</a> <a href="http://rainwarrior.ca/music/coltrane.nes" class="postlink">http://rainwarrior.ca/music/coltrane.nes</a><br /><br />There are also a few threads around this board about the subject if you look for them.</div>

